---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const lastUpdated = 'April 2026';
---
<Base title="Privacy" description="UroRef privacy policy — what data we collect, why, and your rights.">

  <section class="u-hero" style="padding: 5rem 1.5rem 4rem;">
    <div class="u-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="u-hero-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div style="max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative;">
      <div class="u-eyebrow-pill" style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Legal</div>
      <h1 class="u-gradient-text" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 0 0 0.75rem;">Privacy</h1>
      <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-size: 1rem; margin: 0;">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding: 3.5rem 1.5rem 5rem; max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto;">
    <article class="legal">

      <p>
        UroRef is built by Nity G (Urology SpR, North West Deanery). This page explains what
        information the UroRef website (uroref.com) and the UroRef mobile app collect, why,
        and what your rights are. We aim for the absolute minimum.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        Data controller: Nity G, trading as UroRef. Contact via the
        <a href="https://forms.gle/4QTK3MSgMsedJQEw7" target="_blank" rel="noopener">feedback form</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What this website collects</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No account, no login.</strong> The marketing site does not require an account.</li>
        <li>
          <strong>Anonymised analytics</strong> (privacy-respecting, cookie-free — e.g. Plausible /
          Cloudflare Web Analytics). We see aggregate page views, country, referrer, and device
          type. We do <em>not</em> track you across sites and cannot identify you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Feedback form</strong> — if you submit our Google feedback form, the data goes to
          Google Forms under their privacy policy. We use it only to improve UroRef.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What the mobile app collects</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>No personal account.</strong> The app works offline and does not require a login.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Crash + diagnostic data</strong> through the platform (Apple / Google) so we can
          fix issues. This is anonymised and aggregated by the platform.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No clinical data leaves your device.</strong> Anything you pin or favourite is
          stored locally on your phone.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        The website does not set tracking cookies. If we add a privacy-respecting analytics
        provider it will be cookieless. Embedded resources (Google Fonts) may set technical
        cookies — these are not used for tracking.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Hosting — static site host (e.g. Cloudflare Pages / Netlify).</li>
        <li>Google Fonts — to load Inter and JetBrains Mono.</li>
        <li>Google Forms — for feedback collection.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under UK GDPR you have rights of access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability
        and objection. To exercise any of these, contact us via the feedback form. We respond
        within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy materially changes, the "last updated" date above will change and the
        change will be noted on the <a href="/updates">Updates</a> page.
      </p>

      <p class="legal-foot">
        UroRef is a quick reference tool, not a substitute for clinical judgement. Always
        verify against your trust guidelines and seek senior advice where appropriate.
      </p>

    </article>
  </section>

  <style>
    .legal {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.75;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    .legal h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-size: 1.25rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 2.25rem 0 0.6rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }
    .legal p, .legal ul { margin: 0 0 1rem; }
    .legal ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; }
    .legal a {
      color: var(--teal-500);
      text-decoration: underline;
      text-decoration-thickness: 1px;
      text-underline-offset: 3px;
    }
    .legal a:hover { color: var(--teal-400); }
    .legal strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }
    .legal-foot {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      background: var(--navy-700);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--r-md);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
    }
  </style>

</Base>
